<p><img src="/media/13049531/mountain-bar-4.jpg" alt="Mountain Bar 4" width="868" height="416" rel="868,416" /></p>
<p>The art of après ski remains a real cornerstone of the ski holiday and for many it's as important an element of the trip as the skiing itself. <br /><br />For those that don't know, après ski is more a less what it says on the tin, what you do after skiing. Many enjoy finding a bar pumping out music on the slopes or in resort, whilst others prefer a quiet drink or a delectable dish in one of the local pubs or restaurants. <br /><br />So many alpine resorts and venues throw great parties and it’d be a travesty not to seek them out and get involved while you're on holiday! From dancing on tables (both inside and out), to enjoying a cool one in a hot-tub, or enjoying a great meal at an atmospheric restaurant in the middle of the deserted slopes, there really is something for every occasion.</p>
<p>Between us here at Inghams, we’ve covered a fair bit of ground, both on and off the slopes (for educational purposes of course), so we’ve put together some handy Insider's Guides for our <strong>favourite apr<span>è</span>s ski bars and drinks</strong>. Why not try and sample some for yourself?<br /><br />Also, think you know your après ski bars? We've devised a <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://woobox.com/vmkb4a" target="_blank" title="Quiz"><strong>tough quiz</strong></a> to see just how much you love to après - <strong>scroll on</strong> to find out if you're a blue, red, black or diamond après skier! <br /><br />If all this is whetting your appetite, then why not let the experts give you a hand to find your perfect après ski trip?</p>
